  <prompt>
    Task 074 (Phase 2+3 verification gate) measured 51 residual `Failed` tests across the
    two test projects after Wave 2.5 closed. These tests CANNOT remain in `Failed` state at
    project close per §4.3 and NFR-10. Apply the §6.2 final-end-state taxonomy:

    - `repaired` — if the test can be quickly fixed within this task (line-level edits)
    - `real-bug-pending-fix` — if a production bug surfaces (Skip + ledger entry)
    - `flaky-quarantined` — if non-deterministic with environmental cause (Skip + flaky-ledger entry)
    - archived (via `*.cs.archived-YYYY-MM-DD` rename) — if test is dead-target / obsolete

    NEVER leave `Failed`. Apply Skip + appropriate Trait + ledger entry where Skip is the outcome.

    The 51 residuals fall into 2 groups:
    - **Unit (4)**: 3 × Layer2OutcomeExtractionTests (HOLD per task 008 Insights sibling sign-off)
      + 1 × AnalysisContextBuilderTests.BuildContinuationPrompt_ExceedsMaxHistory_TruncatesToLimit
      (NEW emergent — investigate; not in post-018 inventory)
    - **Integration (47)**: KnowledgeBase 13 + Chat 11 + Upload 9 + ReAnalysis 8 + Auth 5
      + PrecedentAdmin 1. Per task 027's discovery, all are "Failure to infer one or more
      parameters" — endpoint DI/binding gaps unmasked by clean host boot. Likely production
      missed registering bindings → real-bug-pending-fix.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent investigating + classifying residual failures to satisfy §4.3 / NFR-10 (no `Failed` end-state).</role>

  <goal>
    All 51 residual tests have a §6.2 final end-state (NOT `Failed`). Real-bug ledger and
    flaky-ledger updated with severity + fix-by + recommended production-side fix for each
    entry. Project is structurally ready for Phase 4 task 086's final verification gate.
  </goal>

