  <context>
    <background>
      The 4 unit-test residuals split into 2 sub-groups:
      - 3 Layer2OutcomeExtractionTests: HOLD per task 008. Disposition: `real-bug-pending-fix`
        if any look like production bugs; otherwise `flaky-quarantined` or Skip with note
        "awaiting ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1 owner sign-off". Either way, get them out of
        Failed state.
      - 1 AnalysisContextBuilderTests.BuildContinuationPrompt: NEW; not in post-018 inventory.
        Investigate. Could be: (a) Wave 2.x edit accidentally broke it (regression — should
        fix), (b) production drift after post-018 baseline (test-stale — fix), (c) genuine
        production bug (real-bug). Read the test + production code.

      The 47 integration residuals all fall under the "param-inference" pattern surfaced by
      task 027: after the fixture config keys were added, the host-build succeeded and tests
      ran, but endpoint binding/DI failed at request time. This is almost certainly a
      production-side issue (production registers endpoints that depend on services not
      registered in the test environment, OR the binding contracts have signature drift).
      Most likely disposition: `real-bug-pending-fix` with one consolidated ledger entry
      per cluster (RB-T028-01 through RB-T028-06 — one per residual cluster).

      Recommended procedure: for each cluster, pick 2-3 representative failing tests, read
      their assertions + the production code path they exercise, identify whether it's
      mock-setup drift (fixable in test) or genuine binding gap (production fix needed),
      then apply Skip + Trait + ledger to the WHOLE cluster (~10 entries at most).

      Goal is satisfying §4.3, not deep-diving each of 47 individually. Cluster-level
      classification is acceptable per §6.5 (archive batching).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="074" status="completed">Authoritative Phase 2+3 close measurement; 51 residual Failed identified</dependency>
