  <steps>
    <step order="1">Parse both post-phase23 TRXs (use PowerShell XPath; do NOT Read 12 MB TRXs into context). Extract each Failed `testName` and `outcome`/`message`. Build a flat list of all 51.</step>

    <step order="2">Group failures by class + namespace. Confirm the breakdown:
      - Unit: 3 Layer2 + 1 AnalysisContextBuilder (= 4)
      - Integration: 13 KB + 11 Chat + 9 Upload + 8 ReAnalysis + 5 Auth + 1 Precedent (= 47)
    </step>

    <step order="3">**Unit residual #1 — Layer2OutcomeExtraction (3 tests)**:
      - Read `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Insights/Layer2OutcomeExtractionTests.cs` (or the actual path; Glob if needed)
      - For each of the 3 failing tests, capture the assertion + failure message from TRX
      - Disposition: `real-bug-pending-fix` IF the failure suggests a production bug; otherwise document as "Skip pending sibling-project sign-off"
      - Apply `[Fact(Skip = "RB-T028-XX: ...")]` + per-test `[Trait("status", "real-bug-pending-fix")]`
      - File RB-T028-01 (or appropriate IDs) in real-bug-ledger.md
    </step>

    <step order="4">**Unit residual #2 — AnalysisContextBuilderTests.BuildContinuationPrompt (1 test)**:
      - Read the test + the production `AnalysisContextBuilder.cs` or equivalent
      - Determine why it fails: assertion-level drift (test-stale → `repaired`)? Or genuine bug (`real-bug-pending-fix`)?
      - Apply the appropriate fix or Skip+ledger
    </step>

    <step order="5">**Integration residuals — bulk cluster classification (47 tests)**:
      - For each of 6 clusters (KB / Chat / Upload / ReAnalysis / Auth / Precedent), pick 2-3 representative failing tests
      - Read the test + the production endpoint code path
      - Identify common root cause per cluster (e.g., "all 13 KB tests fail because production endpoint binding for IKbService is not registered in test env")
      - Apply cluster-level Skip + `[Trait("status", "real-bug-pending-fix")]` to ALL failing tests in that cluster
      - File ONE ledger entry per cluster (RB-T028-02 through RB-T028-07, one per cluster)
      - Severity guidance: HIGH if it's a real production binding gap visible at runtime; MED if it's only test-environment misalignment; LOW if mock-setup drift
    </step>

    <step order="6">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md` with the new RB-T028-NN entries.
      Schema: ID, severity, title, owner-TBD, fix-by date (2026-07-31 or 2026-09-30 depending on severity), test class(es), recommended production-side fix.
    </step>

    <step order="7">Create `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/flaky-ledger.md` if it doesn't exist (with table header). Add entries for any tests classified `flaky-quarantined` (likely 0 in this task; the 51 residuals are all assertion-level, not non-deterministic).</step>

    <step order="8">Re-run targeted tests to confirm:
      - `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Insights.Layer2|FullyQualifiedName~AnalysisContextBuilder"` → expect 0 Failed (some Skipped)
      - `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/` → expect 0 Failed, increased Skipped
    </step>

    <step order="9">Write `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-028-classification-2026-05-31.md` documenting:
      - Per-cluster disposition table
      - Per-test final end-state distribution
      - Ledger entries created
      - Post-classification suite counts (Failed: 0 expected)
    </step>

    <step order="10">Step 9.5 Quality Gates (FULL rigor): code-review on the test edits (Skip + Trait additions only; should be trivial); adr-check (no architectural changes); ledger schema validation.</step>

    <step order="11">Update `current-task.md` + flip task 028 POML `&lt;status&gt;` → `completed` with `&lt;completion-notes&gt;`. Do NOT update TASK-INDEX (main session aggregates).</step>
  </steps>

